snippet: Three million people, three times the estimate, have enrolled in health insurance through private exchanges, according to the consulting firm Accenture.
abstract: Ann Carrns Your Money Adviser; data shows employers are moving more quickly than predicted to offer health insurance to their workers through private exchanges; three million people signed up for workplace health coverage for 2014 through private exchanges, systems that are separate from state and federal health insurance marketplaces.
lead_paragraph: Three million people, three times the estimate, have enrolled in health insurance through private exchanges, according to the consulting firm Accenture.
